flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn operator intent into one bounded, auditable, authoritative run"]
    G2["Make run legitimacy the first real closure point of the platform"]
    G3["Force later phases to inherit a known run basis rather than invent local run scope"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["Operator intent is explicit"]
    E2["platform_run_id is explicit and auditable"]
    E3["scenario_run_id is explicit and deterministic"]
    E4["config payload is explicit"]
    E5["required handle classes must already resolve"]
    E6["The path begins from an explicit control contract, not from runtime discovery"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Control-plane entry"]
    R2["Run identity lock"]
    R3["Config digest validation and commit"]
    R4["Durable run evidence seating"]
    R5["Committed run basis"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["platform_run_id"]
    C2["scenario_run_id"]
    C3["config payload"]
    C4["derived run_config_digest"]
    C5["run evidence references"]
    C6["scenario_run_id comes from a scenario-equivalence seed tied to oracle/source handles and canonicalization rules"]
    C7["run_config_digest is authoritative and is recomputed against the seeded scenario-equivalence contract"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["This is a control-plane path, not a data-plane path"]
    L2["The run exists because the control plane authorized and materialized the run basis"]
    L3["The system does not jump from 'up' to 'streaming' or 'ready'"]
    L4["A pinned run basis is forced first, with explicit pass gates and durable evidence"]
    L5["The rest of the platform is supposed to hang off a known run"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["Step Functions is the control authority"]
    S2["The runbook names Step Functions as the primary runtime for the run-pinned phase"]
    S3["The orchestration layer treats Step Functions as real control authority, not shell glue"]
    S4["S3 provides the durable evidence seating"]
    S5["Pinned run-level prefixes and run-pin artifact locations are explicit in the handles registry"]
    S6["evidence/runs/{platform_run_id}/<br/>run.json<br/>run_pin/run_header.json"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["Config drift must not silently change the meaning of an existing run"]
    Y2["Digest-changing edits force a new platform_run_id rather than mutating the old run"]
    Y3["Canonical payload hashing stops drift between what the run claims to be and what it actually binds to"]
    Y4["Run-lock identity is pinned on orchestrator execution posture"]
    Y5["A separate lock subsystem was avoided to preserve one control authority and avoid authority churn"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. External contract pressure"]
    X1["The data-engine contract distinguishes sealed-world identity from execution correlation"]
    X2["manifest_fingerprint / parameter_hash / seed / scenario_id belong to world identity"]
    X3["run_id belongs to execution correlation"]
    X4["Run-scoped logging correlation must not mutate world outputs whose identity does not include the run"]
    X5["This pushes run identity toward execution scope, control, and evidence rather than source-world mutation"]
    X6["Immutability and gate-before-read fit the commit-once authority of run pinning"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately adds friction"]
    T2["You do not get to 'just run it'"]
    T3["Explicit IDs, explicit config, explicit evidence roots, and explicit handle closure are required before start"]
    T4["This is slower and more ceremony-heavy than a looser setup"]
    T5["The cost buys auditability, replay provenance, and scope discipline"]
    T6["Later behavior is constrained: single active path per phase/run, no in-phase switching, drift forces a new run"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["Without this path, the platform can still be drawn but stops being a serious engineered system"]
    N2["Later phases lose authoritative run basis"]
    N3["No stable config digest exists to explain what was actually run"]
    N4["No durable run-root exists to collect evidence under"]
    N5["Rerun versus identity mutation becomes ambiguous"]
    N6["Daemons might still start and traffic might still flow"]
    N7["But the system would look accidental rather than governed"]
    N8["That is exactly the kind of weakness A is supposed to expose and reject"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["run header committed once"]
    O2["run_config_digest committed"]
    O3["phase evidence root exists"]
    O4["Owned outcome: committed run basis"]
    O5["Outcome is both semantic and material"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>run legitimacy is a required system job"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>the run basis is established through the control plane, with Step Functions and durable evidence"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the path is concretely seated in Step Functions and S3 path contracts"]
    A4["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>config changes, lock semantics, and handle resolution are hard boundaries"]
    A5["Quantified closure claim:<br/>one committed run header<br/>one committed config digest<br/>one run evidence root<br/>zero ambiguity about run basis"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>'this run' becomes a real governed object before anything else in the platform is allowed to matter"]
  end

